he US Country charts, though it did reach number 2 in Canada and led the US Adult Contemporary charts. Rogers then took a break to release a single from his first Christmas album.  \"Blaze of Glory\", which featured [[Kin Vassy]] on backing vocals, was also released as a single.  Although it was a lesser hit than the first two singles, it still made the top ten. The final single, \"Through The Years\", returned Rogers to the very top by putting him at #1 the Adult Contemporary charts once again.\n\nThe album reached #1 on the country charts and #6 on the pop charts, reaching platinum and double-platinum status in the US and Canada, respectively.\n\n{{Album reviews\n|rev1 = [[Allmusic]]\n|rev1score = {{Rating|2.5|5}} [{{Allmusic|class=album|id=r109589|pure_url=yes}} link]\n}}\n\n==Track listing==\n{{tracklist\n|title1 = [[Blaze of Glory (Kenny Rogers song)|Blaze of Glory]]\n|writer1 = Danny Morrison, John Thomas Slate, Larry Keith\n|length1 = 2:37\n|title2 = [[I Don't Need You]]\n|writer2 = Rick Christian\n|length2 = 3:27\n|title3 = The Good Life\n|writer3 = [[Lionel Richie]]\n|length3 = 2:47\n|title4 = Makes Me Wonder If I Ever Said Goodbye\n|writer4 = [[Mickey Newbury]]\n|length4 = 2:29\n|title5 = [[Through the Years (Kenny Rogers song)|Through the Years]]\n|writer5 = [[Steve Dorff]], [[Marty Panzer]]\n|length5 = 4:44\n|title6 = [[Share Your Love with Me]]\n|writer6 = Al \"TNT\" Braggs, [[Deadric Malone]]\n|length6 = 3:19\n|title7 = So in Love with You\n|writer7 = Richie\n|length7 = 4:17\n|title8 = Goin' Back to Alabama\n|writer8 = Richie\n|length8 = 5:04\n|title9 = Without You in My Life\n|writer9 = Richie, [[Thomas McClary (musician)|Thomas McClary]]\n|length9 = 5:04\n|title10 = Grey Beard\n|writer10 = Kenny Rogers, Gene Golden, Kirby Stone\n|length10 = 2:36\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\nCompiled from liner notes.<ref>{{Cite AV media notes |title=Share Your Love |others=Kenny Rogers |year=1981 |type=LP liner |publisher=Liberty Records |id= 134416}}</ref>\n\n;Musicians\n*