{"title_page": "The Mother of Exiles", "text_new": "{{Infobox television episode\n| title          = The Mother of Exiles\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| alt            = \n| series         = [[Westworld (TV series)|Westworld]]\n| season         = 3\n| episode        = 4\n| director       = [[Paul Cameron (cinematographer)|Paul Cameron]]\n| writer         = Jordan Goldberg & [[Lisa Joy]]\n| music          = [[Ramin Djawadi]]\n| photographer   =\n| editor         = \n| production     = 304\n| airdate        = {{Start date|2020|04|05}}\n| length         = 60 minutes\n| guests         = \n| prev           = [[The Absence of Field]]\n| next           = [[Genre (Westworld)|Genre]]\n}}\n\n\"'''The Mother of Exiles'''\" is the fourth episode of the [[Westworld (season 3)|third season]] of the [[HBO]] [[science-fiction]] [[thriller (genre)|thriller]] television series ''[[Westworld (TV series)|Westworld]]''. The episode aired on April 5, 2020. It was written by Jordan Goldberg & [[Lisa Joy]], and directed by [[Paul Cameron (cinematographer)|Paul Cameron]].\n\n==Plot==\n<!-- Per WP:TVPLOT, plot summaries for episode articles should have no more than 400 words. -->\nWilliam suffers a lucid dream with visions of Emily. Charlotte wakes William up, warning him that Serac is trying to take over Delos, and needs him to be present at a board meeting to allow a private investor to buy out the company to protect it. William cleans himself up but has another lucid vision of Emily, but wards it off, saying it was a conscious decision to kill her. As he leaves, Charlotte comments on his vision of Emily, causing him to stop in his tracks.\n\nBernard and Ashley make it to Los Angeles and prepare to infiltrate a private charity event that Liam will be attending, believing he is one of Dolores' swapped hosts. Dolores and Caleb make similar plans but after transferring all of Liam's funds out of his account. At the event, Bernand and Ashley grab Liam after he discovers his funds have been lost, but quickly learn Liam is not a host. Bernard runs off with Liam as Caleb chases him down while Dolores deals with Ashley. Bernard is stopped by guards, but then Martin appears, gunning down the guards. Liam runs off, with Caleb giving chase, while Bernard realizes Martin is the host.\n\nSerac again urges Maeve to help find Dolores, as not only does she hold the encryption key to the Delos data, but also to the Sublime, and Serac says he can reunite Maeve with her daughter. He takes her to Arnold's home to show Maeve that Dolores had made five hosts after leaving the park, and Serac coerces an identiy broker that helped Dolores to give them a lead. Maeve follows this to the \"Mortican\", an [[organ trade]] doctor with ties to the [[Yazuka]]. The Mortican directs her to the Yakuza's headquarters, and after quickly dispatching the guards, Maeve meets the Yakuza leader, Sato, and realizes he is a host as well.\n\nWilliam, Bernard, and Maeve all recognize that Charlotte, Martin, and Sato are host copies of Dolores. Sato tells Maeve that she need to duplicate herself to prevent Serac from stopping her before critically wounding Maeve. William lashes out at Charlotte on his discovery, and Charlotte has his committed to a mental institution, stripping him of his board powers, where he has visions of Dolores as he remembered her from the park. Martin takes Bernard to meet up with Caleb who has cornered Liam, and are soon joined by Dolores, whom Liam recognizes as the girlfriend he had thought dead.\n\n\n==Production==\n\n==Reception==\n\n\n==Notelist==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Portal|Science fiction|Television}}\n* {{URL|1=https://www.hbo.com/westworld/season-3/4-the-mother-of-exiles|2=\"The Mother of Exiles\"}} at [[HBO.com]]\n* {{IMDb episode|10011152}}\n\n{{Westworld}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Absence of Field, The}}\n[[Category:2020 American television episodes]]\n[[Category:Westworld (TV series) episodes]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox television episode\n| title          = The Mother of Exiles\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| alt            = \n| series         = [[Westworld (TV series)|Westworld]]\n| season         = 3\n| episode        = 4\n| director       = [[Paul Cameron (cinematographer)|Paul Cameron]]\n| writer         = Jordan Goldberg & [[Lisa Joy]]\n| music          = [[Ramin Djawadi]]\n| photographer   =\n| editor         = \n| production     = 304\n| airdate        = {{Start date|2020|04|05}}\n| length         = 60 minutes\n| guests         = \n| prev           = [[The Absence of Field]]\n| next           = [[Genre (Westworld)|Genre]]\n}}\n\n\"'''The Mother of Exiles'''\" is the fourth episode of the [[Westworld (season 3)|third season]] of the [[HBO]] [[science-fiction]] [[thriller (genre)|thriller]] television series ''[[Westworld (TV series)|Westworld]]''. The episode aired on March 29, 2020. It was written by Jordan Goldberg & [[Lisa Joy]], and directed by [[Paul Cameron (cinematographer)|Paul Cameron]].\n\n==Plot==\n<!-- Per WP:TVPLOT, plot summaries for episode articles should have no more than 400 words. -->\nWilliam suffers a lucid dream with visions of Emily. Charlotte wakes William up, warning him that Serac is trying to take over Delos, and needs him to be present at a board meeting to allow a private investor to buy out the company to protect it. William cleans himself up but has another lucid vision of Emily, but wards it off, saying it was a conscious decision to kill her. As he leaves, Charlotte comments on his vision of Emily, causing him to stop in his tracks.\n\nBernard and Ashley make it to Los Angeles and prepare to infiltrate a private charity event that Liam will be attending, believing he is one of Dolores' swapped hosts. Dolores and Caleb make similar plans but after transferring all of Liam's funds out of his account. At the event, Bernand and Ashley grab Liam after he discovers his funds have been lost, but quickly learn Liam is not a host. Bernard runs off with Liam as Caleb chases him down while Dolores deals with Ashley. Bernard is stopped by guards, but then Martin appears, gunning down the guards. Liam runs off, with Caleb giving chase, while Bernard realizes Martin is the host.\n\nSerac again urges Maeve to help find Dolores, as not only does she hold the encryption key to the Delos data, but also to the Sublime, and Serac says he can reunite Maeve with her daughter. He takes her to Arnold's home to show Maeve that Dolores had made five hosts after leaving the park, and Serac coerces an identiy broker that helped Dolores to give them a lead. Maeve follows this to the \"Mortican\", an [[organ trade]] doctor with ties to the [[Yazuka]]. The Mortican directs her to the Yakuza's headquarters, and after quickly dispatching the guards, Maeve meets the Yakuza leader, Sato, and realizes he is a host as well.\n\nWilliam, Bernard, and Maeve all recognize that Charlotte, Martin, and Sato are host copies of Dolores. Sato tells Maeve that she need to duplicate herself to prevent Serac from stopping her before critically wounding Maeve. William lashes out at Charlotte on his discovery, and Charlotte has his committed to a mental institution, stripping him of his board powers, where he has visions of Dolores as he remembered her from the park. Martin takes Bernard to meet up with Caleb who has cornered Liam, and are soon joined by Dolores, whom Liam recognizes as the girlfriend he had thought dead.\n\n\n==Production==\n\n==Reception==\n\n\n==Notelist==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Portal|Science fiction|Television}}\n* {{URL|1=https://www.hbo.com/westworld/season-3/4-the-mother-of-exiles|2=\"The Mother of Exiles\"}} at [[HBO.com]]\n* {{IMDb episode|10011152}}\n\n{{Westworld}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Absence of Field, The}}\n[[Category:2020 American television episodes]]\n[[Category:Westworld (TV series) episodes]]\n", "name_user": "Masem", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Mother_of_Exiles"}
{"title_page": "Mary Luarene Browne", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name        = Mary Laurene Browne\n| image       = Mary Laurene Browne.jpg\n| caption     = \n| birth_name  = \n| birth_date  = {{birth-date and age|February 26, 1944}}\n| birth_place = [[Maryland County, Liberia]]\n| alma_mater  = [[Alvernia University]]\n| title       = Sis. and President of Stella Maris Polytechnic University\n| mother      = \n| father      = \n}}\n'''Mary Luarene Browne''' (born February 26, 1944) is a renowned catholic sister, an educator and president of [[Stella Maris Polytechnic University]] in Monrovia.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.liberianobserver.com/news/sis-mary-laurene-browne-clocks-72/|title=Sis. Mary Laurene Browne Clocks 72|last=Admin|first=Webmaster|date=2015-02-26|website=Liberian Observer|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://gnnliberia.com/2016/09/17/gnn-personality-profile-sis-mary-laurene-browne-woman-virtues/|title=GNN Personality Profile: Sister Mary Laurene Browne \u2013 A Woman Of Virtues|last=Brooks|first=Cholo|date=2016-09-17|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref> She is also the author of many textbooks and other publications.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://allafrica.com/stories/201705240879.html|title=Liberia: Sister Laurene Memorializes Angie Brooks With a Biography|date=May 23, 2017|work=allAfrica|access-date=April 6, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=Browne|first=Mary Laurene|url=https://books.google.com/books/about/A_star_from_Suehn.html?id=8OtMAQAAIAAJ|title=A star from Suehn|last2=College|first2=Bishop John Collins Teachers|date=2001|publisher=Bishop John Collins Teachers College, Don Bosco Polytechnic|language=en}}</ref>\n\nMary Luarene Browne was born in Gadetarbo Chiefdom, [[Maryland County]] to Mr. and Mrs. David A. T. Browne and Elizabeth Toe. She developed the nickname \"Little Mary\" by her parents who predeceased her. Her parents divorced when she was six years old.<ref name=\":0\" /> \n\nBrowne first attended the African Methodist Episcopal Parish Day School (AME), and later enrolled at Our Lady of Fatima High school in Maryland County.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.liberianobserver.com/news/sis-mary-laurene-browne-clocks-72/|title=Sis. Mary Laurene Browne Clocks 72|last=Admin|first=Webmaster|date=2015-02-26|website=Liberian Observer|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref> After graduating from high school, she traveled to the United States, where she attended [[Alvernia University]]. Upon the completion of her college education at Alvernia, she entered the Bernadine Franciscan Sisters Convert in [[Reading, Pennsylvania]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.liberianobserver.com/news/sis-mary-laurene-browne-clocks-72/|title=Sis. Mary Laurene Browne Clocks 72|last=Admin|first=Webmaster|date=2015-02-26|website=Liberian Observer|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n", "text_old": "'''Mary Luarene Browne''' (born February 26, 1944) is a renowned catholic sister, an educator and president of [[Stella Maris Polytechnic University]] in Monrovia.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.liberianobserver.com/news/sis-mary-laurene-browne-clocks-72/|title=Sis. Mary Laurene Browne Clocks 72|last=Admin|first=Webmaster|date=2015-02-26|website=Liberian Observer|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://gnnliberia.com/2016/09/17/gnn-personality-profile-sis-mary-laurene-browne-woman-virtues/|title=GNN Personality Profile: Sister Mary Laurene Browne \u2013 A Woman Of Virtues|last=Brooks|first=Cholo|date=2016-09-17|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref> She is also the author of many textbooks and other publications.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://allafrica.com/stories/201705240879.html|title=Liberia: Sister Laurene Memorializes Angie Brooks With a Biography|date=May 23, 2017|work=allAfrica|access-date=April 6, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=Browne|first=Mary Laurene|url=https://books.google.com/books/about/A_star_from_Suehn.html?id=8OtMAQAAIAAJ|title=A star from Suehn|last2=College|first2=Bishop John Collins Teachers|date=2001|publisher=Bishop John Collins Teachers College, Don Bosco Polytechnic|language=en}}</ref> \n\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Mary Laurene Browne\n| image              = [[File:Mary Laurene Browne.jpg|thumb|Mary Luarene Browne]]\n| birth_name         = Mary Laurene Browne\n| birth_date         = February 26, 1944\n| birth_place        = [[Maryland County, Liberia]]\n| nationality        = [[Liberia]]\n| alma_mater         = [[Alvernia University]]\n| title              = Sis. and President of Stella Maris Polytechnic University\n| mother             = \n| father             = \n}}\n\nMary Luarene Browne was born in Gadetarbo Chiefdom, [[Maryland County]] to Mr. and Mrs. David A. T. Browne and Elizabeth Toe. She developed the nickname \"Little Mary\" by her parents who predeceased her. Her parents divorced when she was six years old.<ref name=\":0\" /> \n\nBrowne first attended the African Methodist Episcopal Parish Day School (AME), and later enrolled at Our Lady of Fatima High school in Maryland County.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.liberianobserver.com/news/sis-mary-laurene-browne-clocks-72/|title=Sis. Mary Laurene Browne Clocks 72|last=Admin|first=Webmaster|date=2015-02-26|website=Liberian Observer|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref> After graduating from high school, she traveled to the [[United States]], where she attended [[Alvernia University]]. Upon the completion of her college education at Alvernia, she entered the Bernadine Franciscan Sisters Convert in [[Reading, Pennsylvania]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.liberianobserver.com/news/sis-mary-laurene-browne-clocks-72/|title=Sis. Mary Laurene Browne Clocks 72|last=Admin|first=Webmaster|date=2015-02-26|website=Liberian Observer|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref>\n\n=