bums]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = Once Again It's Christmas\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[Kenny Rogers]]\n| cover      = File:Once Again It's Christmas, Kenny Rogers.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = {{Start date|2015|09|25}}\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Country music|Country]]\n| length     = {{Duration|m=41|s=04}}\n| label      = [[Warner Music Nashville]]\n| producer   = {{flatlist|\n* [[Jim Brickman]]\n* Warren Hartman\n* [[Kyle Lehning]]\n* Darren Rust\n* [[Steve Sundholm]]\n}}\n| prev_title = [[You Can't Make Old Friends (album)|You Can't Make Old Friends]]\n| prev_year  = 2013\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n}}\n'''''Once Again It's Christmas''''' is a holiday album and the 28th and final studio album by [[Kenny Rogers]]. The album features tracks with performances by such musical acts as [[Alison Krauss]] and [[Jennifer Nettles]].<ref>[https://www.rollingstone.com/music/features/kenny-rogers-on-christmas-album-new-hotel-and-obsessive-career-moves-20150929?page=2 Kenny Rogers on Christmas Album, New Hotel and 'Obsessive' Career Moves]</ref>  The album has sold 34,900 copies in the United States as of January 2016.<ref name=\"sales\">{{cite news |url=http://roughstock.com/news/2016/01/39558-top-10-country-albums-chart-january-4-2016 |title=Top 10 Country Albums Chart: January 4, 2016 |first=Matt |last=Bjorke |date= January 2, 2016 |work=Roughstock }}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{tracklist\n| total_length    = 41:04\n| title1          = Once Again It's Christmas\n| note1           = featuring Larry Hall\n| writer1         = Don Russell\n| length1         = 3:56\n| title2          = There's a New Kid in Town\n| note2           = featuring [[Winfield's Locket]]\n| writer2         = [[Don Cook]], [[Curly Putman]], [[Keith Whitley]]\n| length2         = 3:50\n| title3          = Here It Is Christmas/[[Baby, It's Cold Outside]]\n| note3           = featuring Larry Hall and [[Jennifer Nettles]]